\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 44. V. poetica} Boiss. & Spruner in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 1}({\b 6}): 21 (1845). Like {\b 43} but glabrous; leaves up to 2·5cm, oblong-ovate, abruptly contracted into petiole; petiole 3 times as long as lamina; flowers 1-4 per stem, violet or blue.{\i  Rock crevices at} c. 2000{\i  m. Mountains of S.C. Greece} ({\i Fokis, Fthiotis}). Gr.
