\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. V. grisebachiana} Vis., {\i Mem. Ist. Veneto}{\b  10}: 436 (1861). Acaulescent perennial 3-8 cm. Leaves 1·5-3 cm, ovate-orbicular, obtuse, entire or slightly crenate, subglabrous, abruptly contracted into a relatively long petiole. Stipules like the leaves but smaller. Flowers c. 2 cm, basal, violet. Sepals broad, obtuse. Spur 3-4 mm, obtuse, exceeding calycine appendages. 2n = 22.{\i  Alpine meadows. • C. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Ju Bu.
\par

