\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 46. V. alpina} Jacq.,{\i  Enum. Stirp. Vindob.} 159 (1762). Acaulescent perennial 4-10 cm, with a stout stock. Leaves 1·5-3·5 cm, in a basal rosette, ovate-orbicular, crenate, truncate or subcordate at base, obtuse, glabrous, long-petiolate. Stipules 5 mm, oblong or lanceolate, semi-adnate to petiole. Peduncles 2-5 cm. Flowers (1·5-)2-3 cm, violet. Spur 3-4 mm, obtuse, only slightly longer than calycine appendages. 2n = 22.{\i  Alpine meadows and screes; calcicole. •  N.E. Alps; Carpathians}. Au Cz Po Rm.
\par

