\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 47. V. nummulariifolia} Vill.,{\i  Prosp. Pl. Dauph.} 26 (1779). Glabrous, delicate perennial 3-5 cm, with numerous, short, procumbent stems. Leaves 1-2 cm, ovate to orbicular, subcordate, entire; petiole equalling or rather longer than lamina. Stipules c. 5 mm, oblong-lanceolate, acute, the lower entire, the upper remotely dentate. Flowers 1 cm, bright blue. Spur obtuse, about twice as long as the rather short calycine appendages.{\i  Alpine meadows and rocks; calcifuge. • Maritime Alps, Corse.} Co Ga It.
\par

