\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. V. splendida} W. Becker,{\i  Bull. Herb. Boiss.} ser. 2, {\b 2}: 750 (1902). Hairy perennial with ascending stems, 10 cm when young, later up to 50 cm. Lower leaves c. 1½ cm, cordate or subcordate, obtuse; upper 2-3 × 1 cm and more acute, all obtusely crenate and with a long, winged petiole. Stipules half as long as leaves, subpinnate, with 6-10 lanceolate laciniae, the terminal larger and entire. Peduncles 1-3, much longer than the leaves. Flowers 3-4 cm; petals yellow or violet, with rounded apex; spur equalling lower petal, straight, subulate. 2n = 40.{\i  Calcicole. • S. Italy} ({\i mountains near Salerno}). It.
